.com%2F6a19a498b4fb977f3598190d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222688%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESubstack%20threw%20a%20party%20for%20writers%20and%20media%20founders%20in%20New%20York%20City.%3Cp%3ESydney%20Bradley%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ESubstack%20hosted%20an%20all-day%20forum%20on%20the%20state%20of%20media.%20Then%20it%20threw%20a%20party.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20newsletter%20platform%20invited%20its%20own%20writers%2C%20outside%20journalists%2C%20and%20media%20startup%20founders.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHere's%20a%20glimpse%20into%20the%20night%3A%20an%20indoor%20pool%2C%20an%20after-after%20party%2C%20and%20an%20abandoned%20musical%20act.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20day%20with%20Substack%20began%20at%20around%2010%20a.m.%20on%20Thursday%2C%20with%20the%20platform's%20CEO%2C%20Chris%20Best%2C%20telling%20a%20crowd%20of%20writers%20that%20they%20%26quot%3Bdeserve%20to%20get%20rich%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bhave%20fun.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20ended%20a%20little%20past%2010%20p.m.%20at%20a%20podcast%20studio%20office%20space%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsubstack-hamish-mckenzie-working-on-tools-for-bigger-publishers-ankler-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESubstack%20cofounder%20Hamish%20McKenzie%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20eating%20pizza%20with%20the%20lingering%20media%20folk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESubstack's%20big%20day%20was%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsubstack-using-irl-events-with-creators-to-boost-engagement-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efirst-ever%20media%20summit%20%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3BThe%20Once%20and%20Future%20Media%20Forum%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20that%20brought%20together%20the%20newsletter%20platform's%20content%20creators%2C%20journalists%20(like%20me)%2C%20and%20founders%20of%20new%20media%20startups%20in%20a%20sprawling%20five-story%20building%20in%20the%20center%20of%20SoHo%2C%20in%20New%20York%20City.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFeed%20Me's%20Emily%20Sundberg%20kicked%20off%20Substack's%20series%20of%20panels%20by%20interviewing%20TBPN's%20president%2C%20Dylan%20Abruscato%2C%20about%20the%20tech%20talk%20show%20and%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fget-ready-for-wave-of-tbpn-clones-post-openai-deal-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eacquisition%20by%20OpenAI%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Sundberg%20told%20Abruscato%20(who%20also%20worked%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flive-mobile-trivia-game-hq-trivia-reportedly-shutting-down-2020-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EHQ%20Trivia%3C%2Fa%3E)%20that%20his%20work%20was%20like%20that%20of%20the%20Velvet%20Underground%20(in%20that%20the%20rock%20band%20inspired%20many%20others%20to%20start%20bands).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20feel%20like%20the%20projects%20that%20you%20worked%20on%20have%20a%20similar%20influence%2C%26quot%3B%20Sundberg%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Substack%20event%20pool%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a19c03f2ab5f9757add6752%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESubstack's%20branded%20pool%20%E2%80%94%20that%20you%20could%20not%20swim%20in.%3Cp%3EJeremy%20Cohen%3B%20Courtesy%20of%20Substack%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rest%20of%20the%20day%20brought%20media%20figures%20onstage%20to%20talk%20about%20topics%20like%20video%20on%20Substack%20and%20the%20future%20of%20media%20from%20the%20perspective%20of%20content%20creators.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20a%20museum%20of%20media%20artifacts%2C%20a%20swimming%20pool%20you%20could%20ogle%20at%20(but%20were%20forbidden%20to%20swim%20in)%2C%20and%20a%20caf%C3%A9%2Frooftop%20where%20creatives%20prepped%20for%20panels%20downstairs%20and%20sipped%20iced%20coffee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESubstack%20employees%20wore%20lanyards%20with%20signs%20around%20their%20necks%3A%20%3Cem%3EI%20work%20at%20Substack.%20I%20can%20make%20yours%20better.%20Ask%20me%20anything.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20heard%20someone%20refer%20to%20the%20event%20as%20%26quot%3BSubstack%20Coachella.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Free%20Press%20journalists%20working%20at%20Substack's%20event%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a19c03e2e5a80cfe0500c69%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Free%20Press%20journalists.%3Cp%3EJeremy%20Cohen%3B%20Courtesy%20of%20Substack%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20full%20day%20of%20panels%2C%20they%20closed%20the%20event%20with%20a%20%26quot%3BSubstack%20House%20Party%26quot%3B%20with%20trays%20of%20drinks%20and%20bite-sized%20snacks.%20The%20venue's%20rooftop%20kept%20reaching%20capacity%2C%20prompting%20a%20one-in%2C%20one-out%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELet%20me%20take%20you%20into%20the%20night.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20guest%20list%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Media%20people%2C%20talking%20about%20media%2C%20mingling%20with%20other%20media%20people.%20Speakers%20from%20the%20day%2C%20including%20The%20Free%20Press'%20Suzy%20Weiss%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbari-weiss-cbs-news-vision-leaked-all-hands-meeting-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBari%20Weiss%3C%2Fa%3E'%20sister)%2C%20Mad%20Realities%20cofounder%20Alice%20Ma%2C%20and%20actor-writer%20Ben%20Sinclair%20(known%20for%20his%20HBO%20series%20%26quot%3BHigh%20Maintenance%26quot%3B).%20Media%20reporters%20like%20Breaker's%20Lachlan%20Cartwright%20(who%20publishes%20his%20newsletter%20on%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbeehiiv-aims-for-5-million-from-advertising-with-new-funding-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESubstack%20competitor%20Beehiiv%3C%2Fa%3E)%20and%20outlets%20such%20as%20Bloomberg%2C%20Axios%2C%20Semafor%2C%20and%20Adweek.%20Substack-powered%20outlets%20like%20Byline%20and%20The%20Metropolitan%20Review.%20And%20content%20creators%2C%20too%2C%20including%20Substack%20food%20writer%20and%20video%20star%20Caroline%20Chambers%2C%20and%20Wahlid%20Mohammad%2C%20who%20got%20his%20start%20on%20Vine.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20moment%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20As%20the%20venue%20shut%20down%20the%20rooftop%20right%20on%20time%20at%209%20p.m.%2C%20guests%20came%20pouring%20into%20the%20main%20bar.%20Within%20minutes%2C%20we%20were%20all%20kicked%20out%2C%20and%20the%20party%20descended%20down%20the%20several%20flights%20of%20stairs%20and%20gathered%20on%20the%20curb.%20An%20after-after%20party%20was%20swiftly%20thrown%20together%2C%20and%20I%20found%20myself%20with%20a%20gaggle%20of%20Substack%20employees%20(including%20McKenzie%20and%20the%20company's%20events%20connoisseur%2C%20Matt%20Starr)%20and%20creators%2C%20as%20we%20walked%20down%20the%20block%20to%20the%20SoHo%20office%20space%20for%20Osprey%20Studios%20(a%20digital%20media%20and%20podcast%20company).%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20quote%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%26quot%3BIt%20feels%20like%20media%20in%20the%20early%20aughts%2C%26quot%3B%20Mary%20Alice%20Miller%2C%20who%20worked%20at%20Vanity%20Fair%20for%20nearly%20a%20decade%2C%20told%20me%20over%20pizza.%20The%20optimism%20and%20partying%20at%20Substack's%20event%20brought%20back%20memories%20of%20the%20magazine%20parties%20of%20yesteryear.%20%26quot%3BCasual%20hangs%26quot%3B%20like%20the%20one%20unfolding%20were%20also%20commonplace%2C%20Miller%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20gripe%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20There%20was%20a%20promise%20of%20a%20surprise%20special%20musical%20performance.%20I%20was%20enticed.%20Someone%20else%20had%20thrown%20out%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcharli-xcx-brat-autumn-remix-album-explained-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ECharli%20XCX%3C%2Fa%3E%20(who%2C%20notably%2C%20has%20a%20Substack).%20I%20asked%20if%20it%20was%20Bob%20Dylan%20(it%20definitely%20wasn't)%20or%20Jeff%20Tweedy%20(the%20Wilco%20front%20man%20who%20also%20has%20a%20Substack).%20It%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20a%20James%20Brown%20impersonator%2C%20who%2C%20sadly%2C%20never%20got%20a%20chance%20to%20perform.%20Later%2C%20I%20heard%20there%20was%20an%20aspiration%20to%20secure%20Madonna%20for%20the%20night.%20I%20%3Cem%3Ereally%3C%2Fem%3E%20wish%20that%20came%20true.%20Perhaps%20next%20year.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221667%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Substack%20event%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a19d094b4fb977f35981d50%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221250%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESubstack%20employees%20had%20signs.%3Cp%3EJeremy%20Cohen%3B%20Courtesy%20of%20Substack%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWant%20to%20read%20more%20party%20dispatches%20from%20Business%20Insider%3F%20Tag%20along%20with%20our%20reporters%20as%20we%20dive%20into%20the%20social%20scenes%20behind%20tech%2C%20media%2C%20and%20finance%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finside-nyc-ai-psychosis-summit-party-anthropic-claude-code-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAn%20AI%20psychosis-themed%20summit%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyoutube-premiere-kareem-rahma-adam-faze-keep-the-meter-running-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EA%20YouTuber's%20television%20show%20premiere%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdavid-einhorn-tax-day-party-wall-street-dating-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EA%20Tax%20Day%20party%20for%20creatives%20and%20Wall%20Street%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsubstack-summit-media-writers-new-york-party-founders-2026-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1780132081000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a19a4a8b4fb977f3598190f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsubstack-summit-media-writers-new-york-party-founders-2026-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Substack%20loves%20a%20party.%20Tag%20along%20with%20Business%20Insider%20reporter%20Sydney%20Bradley%20as%20she%20spends%20a%20day%20inside%20Substack's%20world.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22sbradley%40businessinsider.com%20(Sydney%20Bradley)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22UP%20Residents%20To%20Pay%2010%25%20Fuel%20Surcharge%20On%20June%20Electricity%20Bills%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22The%20surcharge%20has%20been%20imposed%20to%20recover%20the%20additional%20expenditure%20incurred%20on%20power%20procurement%20and%20transmission%20costs%20in%20accordance%20with%20regulations%20framed%20by%20the%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20Electricity%20Regulatory%20Commission.%22%2C%22published%22%3A1780131961000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Futtar-pradesh-residents-to-pay-10-percent-fuel-surcharge-on-june-electricity-bills-11567984%23publisher%3Dnewsstand%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20surcharge%20has%20been%20imposed%20to%20recover%20the%20additional%20expenditure%20incurred%20on%20power%20procurement%20and%20transmission%20costs%20in%20accordance%20with%20regulations%20framed%20by%20the%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20Electricity%20Regulatory%20Commission.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A99%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Futtar-pradesh-residents-to-pay-10-percent-fuel-surcharge-on-june-electricity-bills-11567984%23publisher%3Dnewsstand%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Futtar-pradesh-residents-to-pay-10-percent-fuel-surcharge-on-june-electricity-bills-11567984%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Futtar-pradesh-residents-to-pay-10-percent-fuel-surcharge-on-june-electricity-bills-11567984%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I'm%20the%20founder%20of%20a%20soju%20brand%20and%20the%20chair%20of%20the%20LACMA%20Art%20%2B%20Film%20Gala.%20I%20work%20between%20Seoul%20and%20LA%20and%20rarely%20sleep%20before%203%20a.m.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228710%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22headshot%20of%20Eva%20Chow%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a18a0502e5a80cfe0500044%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%226532%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEva%20Chow.%3Cp%3ECho%20Gi%20Seok%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Eva%20Chow%2C%20chair%20of%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3Ethe%20Los%20Angeles%20County%20Museum%20of%20Art%20(LACMA)%20Art%20%2B%20Film%20Gala%20and%20founder%20of%20the%20soju%20brand%20KHEE.%20She%20splits%20her%20time%20between%20Seoul%20and%20Los%20Angeles.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20born%20in%20Seoul%20and%20moved%20to%20the%20US%20with%20my%20family%20when%20I%20was%2016.%20I%20built%20my%20career%20in%20New%20York%20as%20a%20fashion%20designer%20and%20later%20owned%20and%20operated%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-chinese-fast-food-chains-across-us-america%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMr.%20Chow%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20luxury%20Chinese%20restaurant%20chain%20that%20operates%20worldwide.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20recognized%20for%20my%20watercolor%20painting%20at%20a%20young%20age%2C%20which%20is%20why%20art%20has%20been%20a%20huge%20part%20of%20my%20life.%20I%20joined%20the%20board%20of%20trustees%20at%20LACMA%20in%202007%2C%20and%20in%202011%2C%20I%20cofounded%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-and-daring-celebrity-looks-at-2022-lacma-artfilm-gala-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EArt%20%2B%20Film%20Gala%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fleonardo-dicaprio-movies-ranked-best-worst-critics%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ELeonardo%20DiCaprio%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20I%20still%20chair%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpower-hours-day-in-the-life-successful-business-leaders-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPower%20Hours%3C%2Fa%3E%20series%20gives%20readers%20an%20inside%20look%20at%20how%20powerful%20leaders%20in%20business%20structure%20their%20workday.%20Reach%20out%20to%20editor%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Flauryn-haas%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELauryn%20Haas%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20share%20your%20daily%20routine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20founded%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kheesoju.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKHEE%20Soju%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202021%20because%20I%20wanted%20to%20share%20my%20Korean%20heritage%20with%20the%20world.%20KHEE%20means%20%26quot%3Benergy%26quot%3B%20in%20Korean%2C%20and%20good%20energy%20is%20central%20to%20how%20I%20live%20and%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20a%20lot%20to%20juggle%2C%20but%20I%20multitask%20and%20manage%20my%20time%20effectively.%20Here's%20a%20day%20in%20my%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b1060c11-7c67-4fef-afbc-b8bea297c12f%5C%22%3EI%20usually%20wake%20up%20around%2010%20a.m.%2C%20no%20matter%20where%20I%20am%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20really%20do%20breakfast.%20In%20the%20morning%2C%20I%20usually%20have%20coffee%20and%20water.%20When%20I'm%20in%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20I%20sometimes%20have%20scrambled%20eggs%20and%20coffee%20in%20bed%2C%20which%20is%20very%20nice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20try%20not%20to%20wear%20makeup%20so%20my%20skin%20can%20be%20its%20natural%20self.%20I%20don't%20like%20covering%20my%20pores.%20In%20the%20morning%2C%20I%20wash%20my%20face%20with%20water.%20Then%20I%20use%20toner%20and%20a%20daytime%20moisturizer%20with%20SPF%2C%20do%20my%20eyebrows%2C%20and%20maybe%20add%20lip%20balm.%20I%20don't%20go%20to%20the%20hair%20salon%20or%20use%20a%20makeup%20artist%20that%20often.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20I'm%20up%2C%20I%20start%20making%20phone%20calls%20and%20replying%20to%20emails%20and%20texts.%20No%20matter%20how%20many%20emails%20I%20answer%2C%20my%20inbox%20never%20seems%20to%20go%20down.%20It's%20the%20same%20with%20texts.%20I%20have%20a%20US%20phone%20and%20a%20Korean%20phone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20listen%20to%20music%20constantly%20while%20I%20work.%20In%20the%20mornings%2C%20I%20mostly%20listen%20to%20classical%20music%20and%20operas%2C%20especially%20piano%20concertos%20and%20piano%20sonatas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f96a01f8-6696-483e-964f-3191a75dd1ed%5C%22%3EI%20don't%20use%20a%20laptop%20much%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20heavy%2C%20and%20I%20can%20do%20almost%20everything%20from%20my%20phone.%20I%20use%20my%20phone%20for%20email%2C%20texts%2C%20WhatsApp%2C%20Telegram%2C%20and%20KakaoTalk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20used%20to%20split%20my%20time%20between%20the%20US%20and%20Seoul%2C%20traveling%20back%20and%20forth%20two%20or%20three%20times%20a%20year.%20Now%2C%20because%20of%20my%20work%20in%20distilling%20and%20developing%20new%20products%2C%20I%20spend%20more%20time%20in%20Korea.%20I%20also%20travel%20frequently%20for%20work%20to%20Southeast%20Asia%20and%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20planning%20the%20next%20LACMA%20Art%20%2B%20Film%20Gala%2C%20which%20will%20be%20on%20November%207%2C%20and%20I%20was%20recently%20in%20LA%20for%20gallery%20openings.%20I%20attend%20several%20board%20meetings%20at%20LACMA%20each%20year.%20It%20takes%20almost%20the%20entire%20year%20to%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20one%20year's%20gala%20is%20done%2C%20I'm%20almost%20immediately%20thinking%20about%20the%20next.%20It%20feels%20like%20a%20labor%20of%20love%20and%20a%20way%20for%20me%20to%20give%20back.%20Through%20that%2C%20I%20help%20raise%20funds%20for%20the%20museum.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20do%20lunch%20either.%20I%20spend%20the%20first%20part%20of%20the%20day%20working%20from%20home%20after%20I%20wake%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2297ec5615-cc89-4e05-803f-fae170738b8e%5C%22%3EBy%20the%20time%20I%20finish%20my%20correspondence%20and%20get%20myself%20together%2C%20it's%20usually%2012%3A30%20or%201%20p.m.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20prefer%20meetings%20after%201%20or%202%20because%20that's%20when%20I%20feel%20more%20relaxed%2C%20whether%20on%20Zoom%20or%20in%20person.%20I%20take%20meetings%20from%20around%202%20p.m.%20to%206%20p.m.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20afternoon%2C%20I've%20answered%20emails%2C%20taken%20care%20of%20myself%2C%20and%20stretched.%20I've%20also%20been%20doing%20physical%20therapy%20because%20I%20broke%20my%20toes%20and%20had%20surgery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2231a31de4-b935-44b8-bf2e-1573aef699a1%5C%22%3EAround%203%20or%204%20p.m.%2C%20I%20start%20getting%20ready%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20day%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERight%20now%2C%20I'm%20very%20focused%20on%20launching%20two%20new%20ready-to-drink%20products%20for%20KHEE.%20My%20main%20focuses%20are%20perfecting%20the%20taste%2C%20designing%20the%20packaging%2C%20and%20overseeing%20many%20details.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20usually%20have%20dinner%20plans%20three%20or%20four%20times%20a%20week%2C%20whether%20with%20friends%2C%20work%20contacts%2C%20or%20both.%20I%20enjoy%20sharing%20a%20meal%20and%20being%20in%20good%20company.%20Recently%2C%20we%20drank%20quite%20a%20bit%20of%20my%20soju%20at%20Simon%20Kim's%20incredible%20new%20place%2C%20Bar%20Chimera.%20I%20had%20so%20much%20fun%20and%20got%20a%20little%20carried%20away.%20That%20was%20later%20than%20most%20nights.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22409bff85-a50a-4c7b-b3a2-0b4c0afe7ae3%5C%22%3EGenerally%2C%20I'll%20head%20home%20around%207%3A30%20or%208%20p.m.%20to%20relax%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20much%20as%20I%20love%20people.%20I'm%20a%20night%20person%20and%20value%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthings-you-need-traveling-alone-frequent-solo-traveler-packing-list-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ealone%20time%3C%2Fa%3E.%20After%20I%20get%20home%2C%20I%20wind%20down%20with%20a%20KHEE%20cocktail%20or%20on%20the%20rocks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'll%20listen%20to%20music%20and%20play%20with%20my%20Pomeranian%2C%20JoJo.%20She's%20only%20three%20pounds%2C%20but%20she%20travels%20everywhere%20with%20me%20and%20can%20handle%20a%2013-hour%20flight%20with%20no%20problem.%20She's%20my%20service%20dog%2C%20my%20security%20dog%2C%20and%20she%20thinks%20she's%20big%20and%20dangerous.%20I%20love%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20like%20to%20watch%20YouTube%20because%20once%20the%20algorithm%20takes%20over%2C%20I%20don't%20have%20to%20choose%20what%20to%20watch%20next.%20I%20leave%20it%20on%20while%20I%20play%20puzzle%2C%20number%2C%20and%20block%20games.%20It's%20how%20I%20relax%2C%20and%20it's%20good%20for%20your%20brain%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20live%20with%20my%20daughter%2C%20and%20she%20tells%20me%20I'm%20like%20a%20millennial%20kid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fc541862-35e3-451a-bc25-04f3c4c4c878%5C%22%3EI%20rarely%20go%20to%20sleep%20before%203%20or%204%20a.m.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I'm%20in%20Korea%2C%20I'm%20speaking%20with%20my%20US%20team%20around%203%20or%204%20a.m.%20When%20I'm%20in%20the%20US%2C%20I'm%20on%20calls%20with%20my%20Korean%20team%20around%202%20or%203%20a.m.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorking%20at%20night%20is%20ideal%3B%20it's%20always%20been%20my%20natural%20rhythm.%20My%20brain%20works%20really%20well%20then.%20I%20can%20be%20in%20shorts%20and%20a%20T-shirt%20with%20nobody%20looking%2C%20and%20I%20feel%20free%20and%20focused.%20I%20do%20a%20lot%20of%20thinking%2C%20writing%20letters%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20a%20very%20productive%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20it's%20been%20a%20late%20night%2C%20I'll%20cleanse%20my%20face%20for%20three%20to%20four%20minutes.%20Then%20I%20use%20toner%20and%20moisturizer%2C%20and%20that's%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20in%20New%20York%20right%20now%20to%20help%20people%20understand%20soju%2C%20especially%20those%20who%20have%20never%20tried%20it%20or%20only%20know%20the%20diluted%20version.%20That%20distinction%20is%20important%20to%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPremium%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fa-korean-rice-liquor-is-far-and-away-the-worlds-best-selling-booze-2012-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esoju%3C%2Fa%3E%20should%20be%20distilled%20and%20simple%3A%20made%20with%20rice%2C%20water%2C%20and%20yeast%2C%20with%20no%20additives.%20I%20think%20people%20are%20ready%20for%20a%20new%20spirit.%20Soju%20is%20part%20of%20my%20heritage.%20I'm%20very%20proud%20of%20where%20I%20come%20from%20and%20of%20what%20I%20make.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fday-life-eva-chow-soju-founder-chair-lacma-gala-2026-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1780131901000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a19a8ef2e5a80cfe0500a20%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fday-life-eva-chow-soju-founder-chair-lacma-gala-2026-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Eva%20Chow%20co-chairs%20the%20LACMA%20Art%20%2B%20Film%20Gala%20with%20Leonardo%20DiCaprio%20and%20runs%20a%20soju%20brand%2C%20KHEE.%20She%20also%20owned%20and%20operated%20Mr.%20Chow.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Kaila%20Yu)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22This%20run-down%20town%20is%20the%20launchpad%20for%20the%20superweapon%20Putin%20used%20to%20attack%20Ukraine%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221880%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Russia%20fired%20its%20Oreshnik%20ballistic%20missiles%20at%20Ukraine%20from%20a%20restricted%20zone%20in%20the%20country's%20southeast.%20Residents%20who%20live%20nearby%20said%20they%20know%20nothing%20about%20the%20launch%20site.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a19a59c2e5a80cfe05009bb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221160%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERussia%20fired%20Oreshnik%20ballistic%20missiles%20at%20Ukraine%20from%20a%20restricted%20zone%20in%20the%20country's%20southeast.%20Residents%20who%20live%20nearby%20said%20they%20know%20little%20about%20the%20launch%20site.%3Cp%3EKremlin%20%2F%20Handout%20%2F%20Latin%20America%20News%20Agency%20via%20Reuters%20Connect%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ERussia%20fired%20its%20Oreshnik%20ballistic%20missile%20at%20Ukraine%20on%20Sunday%20from%20a%20range%20in%20its%20steppe.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20dilapidated%20state%20of%20the%20nearby%20town%20contrasts%20with%20the%20expensive%20missiles%20Russia%20develops%20there.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%26quot%3BNothing%20reaches%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20businesswoman%20in%20the%20restricted%20town%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ERussian%20leader%20Vladimir%20Putin%20has%20ordered%20Oreshnik%20ballistic%20missiles%20to%20be%20fired%20at%20Ukraine%2C%20and%20each%20time%20they%20came%20from%20a%20restricted%20area%20in%20the%20barren%20steppe%20of%20southeastern%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20recent%20Oreshnik%20attack%20came%20on%20Sunday%20amid%20a%20massive%20barrage%20that%20killed%20four%20people%20and%20injured%20many%20more%2C%20according%20to%20Ukrainian%20media.%20Strangely%2C%20the%20powerful%20%2440%20million%20ballistic%20missile%20caused%20only%20a%20smattering%20of%20damage%20to%20a%20garage%20complex%20near%20Kyiv.%20That%20may%20be%20due%20to%20the%20missile's%20armament%20and%20Russia's%20intent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20clue%20about%20the%20missile's%20use%20is%20its%20name%3A%20the%20Russian%20word%20%3Cem%3EOreshnik%3C%2Fem%3E%20means%20%26quot%3Bhazel%20bush.%26quot%3B%20In%20Russia%2C%20hazel%20bushes%20have%20been%20used%20for%20hundreds%20of%20years%20to%20make%20rods%20for%20corporal%20punishment%2C%20a%20Russian%20lawmaker%20recently%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20damage%20from%20the%20May%2024%20attack%20was%20largely%20caused%20by%2090%20missiles%20and%20hundreds%20of%20drones%20heading%20toward%20Kyiv.%20Speaking%20to%20the%20Russian%20outlet%20Vot%20Tak%2C%20political%20scientist%20Oleg%20Saakyan%20estimated%20that%20Russia%20used%20weapons%20worth%20about%20%241%20billion%20that%20night.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Oreshnik%20missile%20struck%20in%20approximately%20six%20clusters%2C%20the%20absence%20of%20explosive%20flashes%20showing%20it%20was%20likely%20armed%20with%20inert%20warheads.%20It%20appears%20to%20be%20a%20demonstration%20of%20raw%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20appears%20that%20none%20of%20those%20projectiles%20have%20any%20explosive%20in%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Pavel%20Podvig%2C%20a%20senior%20researcher%20with%20the%20United%20Nations%20Institute%20for%20Disarmament%20Research.%20%26quot%3BAll%20the%20attacks%20happened%20at%20night.%20Even%20a%20relatively%20small%20explosive%20charge%20would%20produce%20visible%20flashes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20three%20Oreshnik%20missiles%20that%20have%20struck%20Ukraine%20were%20launched%20from%20Kapustin%20Yar%2C%20a%20historic%20missile%20test%20range%20near%20Znamensk.%20The%20small%20town%2C%20with%20just%20under%2030%2C000%20inhabitants%2C%20lies%20about%20700%20miles%20east%20of%20Kyiv%20and%20not%20far%20from%20the%20Kazakhstan%20border.%20Surrounded%20by%20barren%20steppe%20and%20a%20reinforced-concrete%20fence%2C%20the%20town%20is%20a%20so-called%20%26quot%3Bclosed%20administrative-territorial%20area.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20protect%20Russian%20military%20secrets%2C%20no%20one%20may%20enter%20the%20town%20unless%20they%20are%20registered%20there%2C%20have%20been%20expressly%20invited%2C%20or%20have%20undergone%20an%20elaborate%20advance%20registration%20process.%20Anyone%20with%20a%20permanent%20residence%20in%20the%20town%20receives%20a%20pass%20from%20the%20authorities%2C%20featuring%2C%20among%20other%20things%2C%20an%20ascending%20rocket.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20dilapidated%20state%20of%20this%20small%20town%20is%20in%20stark%20contrast%20with%20the%20advanced%20and%20expensive%20missiles%20Russia%20develops%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d4fa616d-fbec-4359-b486-11dde89be257%5C%22%3EA%20run-down%20rocket-town%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222560%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Russia%20has%20used%20the%20Kapustin%20Yar%20range%20to%20test-fire%20intercontinental%20ballistic%20missiles%2C%20like%20the%20one%20seen%20here%2C%20and%20to%20fire%20Oreshniks%20at%20Ukraine.%20The%20restricted%20small%20town%20of%20Znamensk%20is%20nearby.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a19a90ab4fb977f35981981%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOfficials%20test-fired%20an%20intercontinental%20ballistic%20missile%20at%20the%20Kapustin%20Yar%20range.%20The%20restricted%20town%20of%20Znamensk%20is%20nearby.%3Cp%3ERUSSIAN%20DEFENCE%20MINISTRY%2Fvia%20REUTERS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20social%20networks%20such%20as%20X%20and%20Instagram%2C%20several%20unflattering%20images%20of%20Znamensk%20can%20be%20found.%20They%20show%20completely%20run-down%20wooden%20huts%2C%20unpaved%20roads%2C%20apparently%20abandoned%20houses%20with%20smashed%20windows%2C%20and%20a%20Lenin%20statue%20standing%20in%20front%20of%20sagging%20power%20cables.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Russia%2C%20mockery%20erupted%20in%20January%20after%20the%20second%20launch.%20Firing%20an%20Oreshnik%20costs%20at%20least%20the%20equivalent%20of%20%2440%20million%3B%20other%20sources%20put%20the%20figure%20at%20%2460%20or%20even%20%2480%20million.%20Users%20fantasized%20about%20what%20a%20handsome%20town%20the%20Russians%20could%20turn%20Znamensk%20into%20if%20they%20invested%20that%20sum%20into%20proper%20roads%2C%20new%20facades%20and%20modern%20infrastructure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhether%20this%20is%20the%2019th%20or%20the%2021st%20century%3F%20No%20idea%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20user%20wrote.%20Another%2C%20after%20the%20January%20attack%2C%20juxtaposed%20images%20of%20Kapustin%20Yar%20with%20Lviv's%20beautiful%20old%20town%20in%20western%20Ukraine.%20The%20Russians%2C%20he%20wrote%2C%20supposedly%20wanted%20to%20%26quot%3Bliberate%26quot%3B%20Ukraine%20and%20Lviv.%20%26quot%3BHow%20absurd%3A%20perhaps%20Kapustin%20Yar%20should%20be%20liberated%20from%20the%20Russians%20instead.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20X%20user%20wrote%3A%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20exactly%20where%20the%20Russians%20fire%20their%20'hazelnuts'%20at%20Ukraine%20from%20%E2%80%94%20to%20demonstrate%20vividly%20to%20Ukrainians%20and%20the%20whole%20world%20the%20greatness%20of%20so-called%20Russian%20civilization.%20A%20civilization%20that%20considers%20firing%20rockets%20at%20residential%20cities%20the%20highest%20form%20of%20cultural%20expression.%20So%20that%20everyone%20will%20be%20envious.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENevertheless%2C%20Znamensk%20is%20a%20proud%20place.%20Since%201946%2C%20almost%20every%20Soviet%20and%20Russian%20missile%20program%20has%20been%20tested%20at%20the%20range%2C%20formally%20designated%20Military%20Unit%2015644.%20A%20wide%20variety%20of%20missiles%20and%20more%20than%20a%20hundred%20satellites%20have%20been%20sent%20into%20orbit%20from%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20today%2C%20war%20is%20being%20waged%20from%20here.%20Ukraine%20keeps%20the%20test%20range%20under%20constant%20observation%3A%20it%20is%20enough%20for%20the%20Russians%20merely%20to%20simulate%20activity%20at%20the%20training%20ground%20to%20trigger%20an%20air%20alert%20across%20Ukraine.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%20has%20repeatedly%20tried%20to%20damage%20the%20site%20with%20drone%20attacks.%20Apart%20from%20a%20few%20fires%2C%20it%20has%20so%20far%20failed.%20The%20site%20lies%20several%20hundred%20kilometers%20from%20the%20Ukrainian%20border%2C%20leaving%20Ukrainians%20mere%20minutes%20to%20take%20cover.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20residents%20of%20Znamensk%2C%20the%20test%20range%20is%20of%20great%20importance.%20It%20secures%20jobs%20and%20brings%20life%20to%20the%20town.%20Every%20May%2013%2C%20for%20example%2C%20the%20anniversary%20of%20the%20missile%20range%20is%20celebrated%20with%20military%20parades%20and%20ceremonial%20speeches.%20The%20municipal%20%26quot%3BMuseum%20of%20the%20Strategic%20Missile%20Forces%26quot%3B%20organizes%20tours%20and%20festivities.%20Children%20and%20teenagers%20from%20the%20%26quot%3BYoung%20Army%26quot%3B%20also%20visit%20regularly%20%E2%80%94%20a%20kind%20of%20nationwide%20Russian%20leisure%20club%20under%20the%20patronage%20of%20the%20Defense%20Ministry%2C%20which%20puts%20adolescents%20in%20uniforms%2C%20has%20them%20dance%20in%20videos%20for%20the%20fighters%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bspecial%20operation%26quot%3B%20(the%20official%20term%20for%20the%20Ukraine%20war)%2C%20or%20write%20greeting%20letters%20to%20the%20%26quot%3Bliberated%26quot%3B%20children%20of%20Donetsk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22957f5a87-5cb3-4dc9-887d-71f53f2c66a3%5C%22%3E'They%20do%20their%20own%20thing'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224512%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Military%20vehicles%20transited%20through%20the%20Kapustin%20Yar%20training%20range%20during%20a%202020%20exercise.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a19bd5cb4fb977f35981b66%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222874%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMilitary%20vehicles%20transited%20through%20the%20Kapustin%20Yar%20training%20range%20during%20a%202020%20exercise.%3Cp%3EReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20consequences%20for%20the%20residents%20of%20Znamensk%20are%20limited.%20In%20a%20Telegram%20chat%20with%20a%20local%20resident%2C%20it%20was%20said%20that%20the%20local%20population%20is%20involved%20in%20military%20activities%20as%20little%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEverything%20is%20quiet%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20one%20businesswoman.%20%26quot%3BNothing%20reaches%20us.%26quot%3B%20Even%20when%20Ukrainian%20drones%20come%2C%20she%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThey%20turn%20on%20the%20alarm%20and%20notify%20all%20of%20us%20by%20phone.%20No%20reason%20to%20worry.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20she%20couldn't%20say%20what%20happens%20with%20the%20Oreshnik%20missiles.%20%26quot%3BThat%20is%20a%20military%20secret.%20Nobody%20knows%20where%20they%20are%20stationed.%26quot%3B%20And%20even%20if%20someone%20did%20know%20something%2C%20no%20one%20would%20ever%20talk%20about%20it.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20resident%2C%20speaking%20about%20the%20night%20of%20the%20missile%20launch%2C%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20didn't%20hear%20anything.%20They%20do%20their%20own%20thing%20there.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20entirely%20possible%20that%20residents%20do%20not%20notice%20the%20missile%20launches.%20The%20test%20range%20covers%20many%20hundreds%20of%20square%20kilometers%3B%20residents%20of%20Znamensk%20probably%20hear%20little%20more%20than%20a%20distant%2C%20thunder-like%20rumble%20when%20an%20Oreshnik%20is%20launched%2C%20and%20which%20couldn't%20be%20distinguished%20from%20test%20launches.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20missiles%20are%20also%20quickly%20out%20of%20sight%3A%20they%20typically%20climb%20to%20an%20altitude%20of%20several%20hundred%20miles%20and%20reach%20speeds%20of%2013%2C000%20kilometers%20per%20hour%2C%20roughly%2010%20times%20the%20speed%20of%20sound.%20It%20therefore%20takes%20only%20a%20few%20minutes%20to%20reach%20their%20target.%20Other%20states%20learn%20of%20the%20launch%20via%20satellite%20surveillance%2C%20monitoring%20the%20Earth's%20surface.%20On%20infrared%20scans%2C%20the%20exhaust%20plume%2C%20several%20thousand%20degrees%20Celsius%20hot%20and%20rising%20from%20the%20ground%20into%20orbit%2C%20is%20immediately%20visible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223959%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20infographic%20of%20the%20Oreshnik%20ballistic%20missile's%20flight%20profile.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a19bc922ab5f9757add66e8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223633%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20infographic%20of%20the%20Oreshnik%20ballistic%20missile's%20flight%20profile.%3Cp%3EGraphic%20by%20AFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Russians%20in%20Znamensk%20can%20lead%20quiet%20lives.%20They%20play%20in%20volleyball%20tournaments%20in%20the%20sports%20hall%20attached%20to%20the%20administrative%20wing%20of%20the%20test%20range.%20They%20can%20walk%20in%20the%20%26quot%3BFairy-Tale%20Glade%26quot%3B%20park%2C%20where%20several%20life-sized%20rocket-shaped%20monuments%20are%20arranged%20around%20a%20fountain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20victims%20of%20the%20missiles%20manufactured%20here%20are%20primarily%20Ukrainians.%20But%20neighbors%20in%20Kazakhstan%20are%20also%20severely%20affected.%20Russia%20has%20leased%20parts%20of%20western%20Kazakhstan%20as%20an%20extension%20of%20the%20test%20range%20%E2%80%94%20the%20contract%20currently%20runs%20until%202030.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20local%20Kazakhs%2C%20the%20lease%20of%20the%20land%20has%20serious%20consequences.%20As%20the%20Russian%20newspaper%20Novaya%20Gazeta%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnovayagazeta.eu%2Farticles%2F2024%2F02%2F21%2Fkapustin-iad%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202024%2C%20Russia%20prefers%20to%20test%20its%20missiles%20over%20Kazakh%20territory.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20missile%20parts%20and%20fuel%20fall%20into%20the%20steppe%2C%20causing%20fires%2C%20killing%20livestock%2C%20and%20contaminating%20soil%20and%20water.%20The%20steppe%20is%20littered%20with%20craters%3B%20no%20recultivation%20takes%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20have%20now%20found%20that%20cancer%20rates%20in%20the%20region%20are%20above%20average.%20Neurological%20damage%20and%20disabilities%20among%20children%20are%20strikingly%20common.%20State%20assistance%20from%20Kazakhstan%20is%20practically%20nonexistent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EJulius%20Fitzke%2C%20a%20trainee%20at%20WELT%20in%20the%20foreign%20affairs%20department%20since%20July%202025%2C%20lived%20in%20Russia%20for%20three%20years.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frundown-town-is-the-launchpad-for-russias-oreshnik-missile-2026-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1780131361000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a19beaa2ab5f9757add671a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frundown-town-is-the-launchpad-for-russias-oreshnik-missile-2026-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Russia%20fired%20its%20Oreshnik%20missile%20at%20Ukraine%20on%20Sunday%20from%20a%20remote%20range.%20Residents%20of%20the%20nearby%20town%20say%20the%20consequences%20have%20been%20limited.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Insider%20Inc.)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A99%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Centre%20plans%20farmer%20outreach%20campaign%20from%20June%20on%20soil%20over%20El%20Nino%20worry%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1780131312000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2025-05%2F19%2Fthumb%2Ffitandfill%2F1200X628%2F1747638215-6795.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findustry%2Fagriculture%2Fsave-the-fields-campaign-monsoon-el-nino-farmer-advisories-126053000736_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Centre%20will%20begin%20a%20month-long%20'Save%20the%20Fields'%20campaign%20from%20June%201%2C%20offering%20crop-specific%20advisories%20and%20climate-resilient%20farming%20gu