Fno-dignity-matt-walsh-erupts-over-erika-kirk-boyfriend-rumor-while-blake-wynn-breaks-silence%2Farticleshow%2F131401645.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia-indiatimes-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus-streamers%2Fno-dignity-matt-walsh-erupts-over-erika-kirk-boyfriend-rumor-while-blake-wynn-breaks-silence%2Famp_articleshow%2F131401645.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus-streamers%2Fno-dignity-matt-walsh-erupts-over-erika-kirk-boyfriend-rumor-while-blake-wynn-breaks-silence%2Famp_articleshow%2F131401645.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20survived%20breast%20cancer.%20I%20wasn't%20prepared%20for%20what%20came%20next.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222316%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20author%20poses%20in%20her%20home.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a19ab8d2e5a80cfe0500a7b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221737%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20said%20that%20she%20is%20grateful%20to%20have%20been%20in%20remission%20for%20five%20years%2C%20but%20surviving%20cancer%20is%20hard%20in%20ways%20she%20wasn't%20expecting.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Rachel%20Garlinghouse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EI%20just%20had%20my%20anniversary%20and%20can%20say%20I%20have%20been%20in%20remission%20from%20breast%20cancer%20for%20five%20years.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EI%20am%20grateful%20for%20my%20health%2C%20but%20there%20are%20so%20many%20hard%20things%20about%20surviving%20cancer.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EFear%20of%20recurrence%20and%20survivor's%20guilt%20are%20constantly%20on%20my%20mind.%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20big%20day%20finally%20arrived%2C%20the%20day%20I%20could%20say%20I'd%20been%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwife-cancer-remission-caregiver-trauma-after-treatment-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebreast%20cancer%20remission%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20five%20years%2C%20I%20wasn't%20as%20ecstatic%20as%20I%20thought%20I'd%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20a%20regular%20Tuesday%2C%20and%20I%20had%20to%20take%20my%20kids%20to%20school%20and%20go%20to%20work.%20There%20was%20no%20fanfare.%20I%20was%20here%2C%20I%20was%20healthy%2C%20and%20I%20had%20to%20get%20on%20with%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparental-burnout-millennial-most-exhausted-generation-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edaily%20life%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20reality%20is%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foncologist-breast-cancer-tips-how-to-reduce-lower-risk-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebreast%20cancer%20fighters%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20survivors%20are%20often%20labeled%20as%20inspirational%20warriors.%20We%20fight%20the%20battle%20%26quot%3Blike%20a%20girl%2C%26quot%3B%20with%20pink%20boxing%20gloves%20on%2C%20our%20heads%20bald%2C%20but%20our%20grins%20wide.%20However%2C%20the%20reality%20is%20that%20there%20are%20so%20many%20hard%20things%20about%20surviving%20cancer%20that%20no%20one%20warned%20me%20about.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2216f4f092-a211-4266-8f5f-8189106931e2%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou%20never%20%26quot%3Bget%20over%26quot%3B%20having%20cancer%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20my%20first%20breast%20cancer%20battle%2C%20I%20wound%20up%20choosing%20to%20do%20EMDR%2C%20a%20specialized%20type%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freference%2Fwhat-is-emdr%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etrauma%20therapy%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20wasn't%20officially%20diagnosed%2C%20but%20was%20strongly%20suspected%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstop-trauma-dumping-on-me-just-because-i-had-cancer-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehave%20PTSD%20%3C%2Fa%3Eas%20a%20result%20of%20my%20initial%20diagnosis.%20After%20several%20sessions%20of%20EMDR%2C%20I%20started%20to%20feel%20safer%2C%20more%20confident%2C%20and%20less%20like%20a%20cancer%20patient..%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20I%20fared%20better%20mentally%20the%20second%20time%20around%2C%20about%20three%20years%20after%20my%20first%20breast%20cancer%20diagnosis%2C%20the%20cancer%20shadow%20is%20always%20lurking%20in%20the%20background%2C%20sometimes%20popping%20up%20when%20I%20least%20expect%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22720%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20author%20during%20cancer%20treatment.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a19ac272ab5f9757add6566%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20said%20that%20sounds%20can%20trigger%20memories%20of%20the%20hardest%20days%20of%20her%20cancer%20treatment.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Rachel%20Garlinghouse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20day%2C%20I%20pulled%20up%20to%20my%20favorite%20coffee%20shop%20to%20grab%20a%20coffee%20via%20the%20drive-thru.%20As%20I%20waited%2C%20one%20of%20the%20coffee%20timers%20started%20going%20off%2C%20and%20I%20immediately%20started%20panicking.%20This%20is%20because%20the%20timer%20sounded%20eerily%20similar%20to%20the%20timers%20on%20the%20IV%20poles%20at%20my%20chemo%20infusion%20center.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20know%20when%20these%20fears%20or%20memories%20may%20pop%20up%2C%20but%20it's%20always%20a%20possibility%20lurking%20in%20the%20background.%20I%20sometimes%20wonder%20if%20this%20is%20something%20I'll%20eventually%20get%20over%2C%20but%20for%20now%2C%20I%20know%20I%20have%20to%20live%20with%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222f59a7a5-03ec-481c-822e-3021c9188d41%5C%22%3E%3Cbr%3E%3Cstrong%3ECancer%20continues%20to%20be%20expensive%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrue-cost-young-colon-cancer-crisis-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EFighting%20cancer%20%3C%2Fa%3Eis%20financially%20draining%2C%20even%20with%20excellent%20health%20insurance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20dozens%20of%20lab%2C%20surgery%2C%20exam%2C%20chemo%2C%20heart%20scan%2C%20and%20radiation%20appointments%20in%20the%20span%20of%20about%2018%20months.%20Even%20after%20hitting%20my%20out-of-pocket%20max%2C%20we%20had%20to%20pay%20for%20the%20gas%20(and%20wear%20and%20tear%20on%20our%20car)%20to%20travel%20to%20all%20those%20appointments.%20Additionally%2C%20I%20didn't%20work%20for%20about%20six%20months%20while%20I%20was%20in%20chemo%2C%20and%20then%20proceeded%20with%20thirty-three%20rounds%20of%20radiation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20after%20active%20treatment%20days%20are%20over%2C%20there%20are%20still%20all%20the%20follow-up%20scans%2C%20exams%2C%20and%20labs%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feven-with-insurance-my-breast-cancer-treatment-was-expensive-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethose%20add%20up%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20spent%20a%20year%20investigating%20the%20rise%20in%20young%20cancers%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20financial%2C%20emotional%2C%20and%20systemic%20costs%20that%20come%20with%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESee%20more%20in%20our%20series%2C%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20True%20Cost%20of%20Young%20Cancer%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrue-cost-young-colon-cancer-crisis-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ECancer%20rates%20are%20rising%20among%20young%20adults.%20The%20healthcare%20system%20can't%20keep%20up%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyoung-cancer-work-career-impact-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EFor%20young%20cancer%20patients%2C%20work%20is%20a%20lifeline%20%E2%80%94%20and%20a%20burden%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fidentical-twins-young-colon-cancer-diagnosis-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EThese%20twins'%20lives%20were%20identical%2C%20until%20one%20got%20colon%20cancer%20at%2021%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyoung-cervical-cancer-diagnosis-marriage-motherhood-finances-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EShe%20was%2035%20with%20a%20new%20baby%20when%20cancer%20hit.%20Her%20family%20is%20still%20paying%20the%20price%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyoung-cancer-fertility-preservation-egg-sperm-freezing-state-laws-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EYoung%20cancer%20patients%20face%20a%20brutal%20choice%20if%20they%20want%20to%20have%20children%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DjXZaBv3po-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVIDEO%3A%205%20young%20colon%20cancer%20patients%20share%20their%20life%20lessons%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227421c763-8f39-4d32-a586-fdfbc451659b%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMy%20greatest%20fear%20is%20recurrence%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20survivor%20knows%20that%20our%20greatest%20fear%2C%20one%20that's%20a%20reality%20for%20some%2C%20is%20that%20the%20cancer%20can%20come%20back.%20Every%20time%20I%20have%20basic%20labs%20drawn%20or%20go%20for%20my%20yearly%20CT%20scan%2C%20all%20my%20old%20fears%20come%20rushing%20back%2C%20and%20my%20brain%20begins%20to%20play%20the%20what-if%20game.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELikewise%2C%20I%20worry%20about%20how%20we%20will%20pay%20for%20more%20treatment%2C%20how%20another%20battle%20would%20impact%20my%20children%2C%20and%20what%20I%20would%20do%20for%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222316%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20author%20at%20a%20doctor's%20appointment.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a19ad1fb4fb977f35981a1a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221737%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThough%20she%20often%20puts%20on%20a%20happy%20face%2C%20the%20author%20admits%20she%20has%20fears%20of%20recurrence%20every%20time%20she%20feels%20pain%20or%20goes%20in%20for%20a%20checkup.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Rachel%20Garlinghouse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22127d4ae4-a981-4b66-b65b-08fc7117076d%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESurvivor's%20guilt%20is%20real%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFive%20years%20is%20a%20major%20milestone%20in%20surviving%20cancer%2C%20and%20I%20am%20certainly%20very%20grateful%20to%20have%20made%20it%20this%20far.%20However%2C%20the%20longer%20I've%20been%20a%20survivor%2C%20the%20more%20thrivers%2C%20fighters%2C%20and%20survivors%20I've%20chosen%20to%20follow%20on%20social%20media%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20more%20women%20I've%20befriended%20in%20real%20life.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20reality%20is%2C%20the%20cancer%20does%20come%20back%20for%20some.%20Is%20there%20some%20secret%20relief%20that%20this%20time%2C%20it's%20not%20me%3F%20Yes.%20But%20it's%20also%20heartbreaking%20to%20watch%20the%20battles%20of%20others%2C%20including%20those%20whose%20souls%20leave%20the%20world%20from%20this%20terrible%20disease.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESociety%20wants%20me%20to%20wear%20pink%20and%20continue%20to%20be%20a%20beacon%20of%20light%20and%20hope%20as%20someone%20who%20%26quot%3Bwon%26quot%3B%20the%20battle.%20I%20am%20certainly%20happy%20that%20the%20day%20I%20prayed%20for%20is%20here%2C%20an%20anniversary%20that%20seemed%20unattainable%20years%20ago.%20Yet%2C%20I%20continue%20to%20understand%20that%20two%20things%20can%20be%20true%20at%20the%20same%20time.%20I%20can%20be%20thankful%20for%20survivorship%20and%20simultaneously%20heartbroken%20at%20all%20cancer%20took%20and%20still%20takes%20from%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsurvived-breast-cancer-wasnt-prepared-for-what-came-next-guilt-2026-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1780093261000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a19aba22ab5f9757add6554%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22