%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIron%20Lung%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20movie%2C%20which%20he%20made%20for%20a%20reported%20%243%20million%20and%20has%20now%20grossed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.boxofficemojo.com%2Ftitle%2Ftt27564844%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%2450%20million%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJournalism%20Rules%20require%20me%20to%20point%20out%20that%20three%20things%20make%20up%20a%20bona%20fide%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2026%2F05%2F29%2Fbusiness%2Fmedia%2Fbackrooms-film-youtube.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etrend%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20I%20think%20we're%20actually%20talking%20about%20two%20different%20ideas%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EWhen%20Fischbach%20made%20his%20movie%2C%20he%20self-financed%20and%20produced%20the%20whole%20thing%2C%20and%20asked%20his%20fans%20for%20help%20with%20distribution%20as%20well.%20Going%20to%20see%20%26quot%3BIron%20Lung%26quot%3B%20was%20something%20you%20did%20because%20you%20liked%20Markiplier%20and%20wanted%20to%20support%20him.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EParsons%20and%20Barker%20also%20benefit%20from%20YouTube%20fandom.%20But%20their%20followings%20there%20are%20smaller%20than%20Fischbach's.%20More%20important%3A%20They%20are%20actively%20working%20within%20the%20Hollywood%20system%2C%20by%20making%20movies%20with%20established%20studios%20%E2%80%94%20A24%20for%20%26quot%3BBackrooms%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fblumhouse-founder-ai-wont-improve-movies-but-cant-be-ignored-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBlumhouse%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20%26quot%3BObsession.%26quot%3B%20That%20looks%20a%20lot%20more%20like%20Hollywood%20using%20YouTube%20as%20a%20farm%20team%2C%20where%20it%20can%20pluck%20promising%20online%20prospects%20and%20give%20them%20a%20shot%20at%20the%20big%20leagues.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhich%20isn't%20a%20new%20idea.%20Mainstream%20media%20has%20been%20using%20the%20internet%20broadly%20and%20YouTube%20specifically%20as%20an%20incubator%20for%20years%2C%20which%20is%20why%20you%20know%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DkffacxfA7G4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJustin%20Bieber%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fplaylist%3Flist%3DPL854514FC0EBDCD8E%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIssa%20Rae%3C%2Fa%3E%20are.%20It's%20true%20for%20directors%2C%20too%3A%20Dan%20Trachtenberg%2C%20who%20made%20last%20year's%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.20thcenturystudios.com%2Fmovies%2Fpredator-badlands%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPredator%3A%20Badlands%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20announced%20himself%20to%20Hollywood%20back%20in%202011%2C%20with%20a%207-minute%20short%20based%20on%20the%20video%20game%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3D4drucg1A6Xk%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPortal%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20seems%20quite%20likely%20we%20will%20see%20a%20lot%20more%20of%20the%20%26quot%3BBackrooms%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BObsession%26quot%3B%20model%2C%20simply%20because%20%26quot%3Bmaking%20movies%20and%20putting%20them%20on%20YouTube%26quot%3B%20is%20such%20an%20obvious%20route%20for%20any%20young%20filmmaker.%20Martin%20Scorsese%20would%20have%20done%20the%20same%20thing%2C%20if%20he%20started%20out%20with%20an%20iPhone%20and%20a%20broadband%20connection.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20me%2C%20the%20more%20intriguing%20question%20is%20whether%20we%20will%20see%20more%20Markipliers%3A%20people%20who%20develop%20real%20followings%20on%20YouTube%20(or%20any%20other%20digital%20platform)%20who%20can%20convince%20their%20followers%20to%20look%20up%20from%20their%20phones%20and%20buy%20tickets%20to%20something.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20remains%20rare%2C%20but%20less%20than%20it%20used%20to%20be%2C%20which%20is%20why%20it's%20no%20longer%20shocking%20when%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Fnewsletters%2F2025-08-28%2